Subject: [PATCH] refactor(skills): drop dead 'skillModifiers' field + sync
 docs/schema/03,04
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Audit of docs/schema/03-attributes-skills.md and 04-derived.md against
the actual code showed that most of the contract is already done; the
only real debt was the dead field 'skillModifiers'.

Findings:
  - 'skillModifiers' was declared in GhoulModal.handleConfirm and stored
    on data/traits/traits.json (ghoul-necrotic-posthuman), but NO code
    ever read it. canChangeSkillValue / validateSkills only look at
    'skillMaxValue'. So the +2 SURVIVAL bonus implied by the field was
    pure data ceremony.
  - Right next to it sat forcedSkills: ['SURVIVAL'] + extraSkills: 1,
    which (per owner's call) IS the correct way to model an extra-tagged
    skill: forcedSelectedSkills + tag → automatic +2 to value and a
    distinct UI highlight (extra-tagged).
  - All other items in 03 (attribute Parameter shape, attributeBonus,
    attributeLimits, attributePointsBonus, canonical UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
    skill keys) are already implemented and now marked ✅ in the schema.
  - 04-derived contract (maxHealth / initiative / defense / meleeBonus /
    carryWeight human+robot / damageResistance with timed-effect
    modifiers, Parameter shape) is fully implemented (D-2 closed).
  - AS-1 (combining multiple sources of attributeLimits) is N/A: only
    one source exists today (trait). Re-opens when perks/chems land.
  - D-1 (ghoul radiation-as-healing) is still an open gameplay design
    decision — left as ☐ in 04 for a separate gameplay pass.

Changes:

  1) components/screens/CharacterScreen/modals/traits/GhoulModal.js
     Drop 'skillModifiers: { SURVIVAL: 2 }' from onSelect payload. Add
     comment explaining that the tag mechanic already supplies the +2.

  2) data/traits/traits.json (ghoul-necrotic-posthuman)
     Remove dead 'skillModifiers' block from modifiers.

  3) domain/contract.skills.test.js
     Drop SKILL_MAP_FIELDS entry — there are no skillModifiers-style
     map-of-skill fields in data anymore. Test still verifies all
     skill-id strings & lists are canonical UPPER_SNAKE_CASE.

  4) docs/schema/03-attributes-skills.md
     Mark ✅ everywhere the implementation matches the contract.
     Explicit § 'Удалено: skillModifiers (AS-3)' with rationale.
     Note AS-1 as N/A until a second source of attributeLimits appears.

  5) docs/schema/04-derived.md
     Mark ✅ on every Parameter-shaped derived stat and on the timed-
     effects integration. Close D-2 (Parameter shape) — already done.
     Leave D-1 (radiation-heals-ghoul) as the only ☐ in 04, with a
     clear list of design decisions needed before implementation.

No new behavior; this is a contract clean-up + dead-field removal.
